body: Open to suggestions for how to test these.

comment_data.body: This needs to be declared `inline`, because that's the intention after all.
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -24,7 +24,33 @@ cdef extern from "datetime.h":
         pass
 
     ctypedef extern class datetime.datetime[object PyDateTime_DateTime]:
-        pass
+        @property
+        cdef int year(self):

comment_data.body:
```suggestion
@cython.test_fail_if_path_exists(
    "//CoerceFromPyTypeNode",
    "//AttributeNode",
)
def test_datetime_attrs_inlined(datetime dt):
    # GH#3737
    """
    >>> py_dt = datetime(2020, 8, 18, 4, 9)
    >>> dt = test_datetime_attrs_inlined(py_dt)
    >>> dt[:5]
    (2020, 8, 18, 4, 9)
    >>> dt[5] == py_dt.second  or  (dt[5], py_dt.second)
    True
    >>> dt[6] == py_dt.microsecond  or  (dt[6], py_dt.microsecond)
    True
    """
    return (
        dt.year,
        dt.month,
        dt.day,
        dt.hour,
        dt.minute,
        dt.second,
        dt.microsecond,
    )
```
